groups.title: SD 3.5-MEDIUM (mainly for compairson -uses sd3.5 medicum for low vram machines)
Aura Flow (TRUE OPEN SOURCE - but still very beta, and slightly slow)
PixArt (VERY FAST, AND ARTSY, but not so Realistic many times)
Hunyuan - (DESCENT output, but looks like prints in old books too often due to Eastern look of things.  Slightly slower than Flux Pixart, Slightly faster than Flux GGUF)
MOCHI-VIDEO (time consuming but beautiful output video)
SDXL-NO REFINER - (old school - mainly here for comparisons)
FLUX-GGUF METHOD (MAINLY USE THIS FOR FLUX)
SDXL WITH REFINER (i.e. Comfy From Scratch Part 3 as listed at https://followfoxai.substack.com/p/part-3-sdxl-in-comfyui-from-scratch )
OUTPAINT FOOCUS STYLE (SDXL Output) Utilizes Foocus outpainting modification to ComfyUI that's described at  https://github.com/Acly/comfyui-inpaint-nodes
FLUX GGUF-RUN 2-OUTPUT (uses WD14-Tagger Node to re-imagine the scene)\
SVD-VIDEO -(IMAGE BASED) (Old School Video - slightly blury, but neat - requires about an hour or so to render)
